faqs:
  - title: What security certifications does Clientify have?
    description: >
      Clientify maintains ISO/IEC 27001:2022 certification by Bureau Veritas, 
      originally approved March 2021 with current certificate valid through
      March 2027.  The certification covers their Information Security
      Management System supporting  development, support, maintenance, and
      hosting of the digital marketing platform.  Additionally, Clientify has a
      Comply.org Trust Center with independent legal  and technical security
      reviews (August 2024) by CIPP/E certified attorney and  CIPT certified
      privacy engineer.
  - title: Where is Clientify's data processed?
    description: >
      Clientify is headquartered in Almeria, Spain within the European Union, 
      ensuring data processing under EU jurisdiction and GDPR compliance.
      Infrastructure  is hosted on Amazon Web Services and Digital Ocean.
      International data transfers  to US-based subprocessors (Google Analytics,
      Intercom, Sendgrid, payment  processors) are protected by Standard
      Contractual Clauses and appropriate  safeguards verified through
      Comply.org review.
  - title: How does Clientify handle data subject requests?
    description: >
      Clientify has established procedures for handling GDPR data subject
      requests  including access, rectification, erasure, portability, and
      objection rights.  Response processes are defined with verification
      procedures and timelines  aligned with ISO 27001 requirements and
      Comply.org attestation. Contact the  DPO at dpo@clientify.com for data
      subject inquiries.
  - title: What is Clientify's approach to third-party risk management?
    description: >
      Clientify implements comprehensive supply chain risk management covering
      13  documented subprocessors including infrastructure providers (AWS,
      Digital Ocean),  communication tools (Intercom, Sendgrid), payment
      processors (Stripe, PayPal,  GoCardless), and analytics (Google
      Analytics). All vendors are documented in  Comply.org Trust Center with
      formal agreements including security requirements  and data protection
      clauses.
  - title: Does Clientify have AI features and how are they governed?
    description: >
      Yes, Clientify offers AI-powered features including chatbot with IA,
      commercial  proposals with IA, contact enrichment with IA, and planned
      landing pages with IA.  AI usage is governed by documented Terms of Use
      (Condiciones de Uso de la IA)  establishing user responsibilities, content
      generation disclaimers, privacy  protections, and compliance with data
      protection regulations. Users are responsible  for not introducing
      sensitive data without proper authorization.
  - title: What Information Security Management System does Clientify use?
    description: >
      Clientify implements an SGSI (Sistema de Gestión de Seguridad de la
      Información)  certified under ISO/IEC 27001:2022 by Bureau Veritas. The
      system includes  documented Information Security Policy (SGSI-PSI-01),
      risk management procedures,  security controls, incident response,
      business continuity, and regular audits.  Certification covers all
      processes supporting the digital marketing platform  with annual
      surveillance audits.
  - title: Who are Clientify's privacy and security reviewers?
    description: >
      Clientify's Comply.org Trust Center has been independently reviewed by
      certified  professionals: Legal assessment by CIPP/E certified attorney
      (IE4322) validating  GDPR compliance and data protection principles, and
      Technical assessment by  CIPT certified privacy engineer (PE4951)
      validating security measures and  technical controls. Latest review:
      August 27, 2024. These reviews complement  ISO 27001:2022 certification
      audits by Bureau Veritas.
  - title: What payment processing options does Clientify use?
    description: >
      Clientify uses multiple payment processors to serve global customers:
      Stripe  and PayPal for general transactions, and GoCardless for direct
      debit payments  (UK/EU). All payment processors are documented
      subprocessors with formal data  processing agreements, security controls
      verified through Comply.org review,  and compliance with PCI DSS standards
      for handling payment card information.
